  "akureyri.C.list.2.bio": "Elías Gunnar Þorbjörnsson is headteacher of Giljaskóli in Akureyri and is in 2nd place on Viðreisn’s list in the 2026 municipal elections. He has written about education issues in Akureyri and emphasises evidence-based improvements in school practice.",
  "akureyri.C.list.2.occupation": "Headteacher",
  "akureyri.C.list.20.occupation": "Tour guide",
  "akureyri.C.list.21.occupation": "Doctor",
  "akureyri.C.list.22.occupation": "General practitioner — retired",
  "akureyri.C.list.3.bio": "Þóroddur Ingvarsson is a doctor, specialist in anaesthesia and intensive care medicine, and is in 3rd place on Viðreisn’s list in Akureyri. He has written about the importance of municipalities creating opportunities for children and young people to develop and grow.",
  "akureyri.C.list.3.occupation": "Anaesthesiologist and intensive care physician",
  "akureyri.C.list.4.bio": "Elísabet Ögn Jóhannsdóttir is a cultural affairs project manager and is in 4th place on Viðreisn’s list in Akureyri in the 2026 municipal elections. She emphasises cultural life and the development of Akureyri as a cultural centre for North Iceland.",
  "akureyri.C.list.4.occupation": "Cultural affairs project manager",
  "akureyri.C.list.5.bio": "Íunn Eir Gunnarsdóttir holds a master’s degree in leisure studies and development work and is in 5th place on Viðreisn’s list in Akureyri. She has proposed the establishment of an academy of excellence for lower secondary students to promote sports, the arts and culture on an equal footing.",
  "akureyri.C.list.5.occupation": "Leisure and social studies specialist",
  "akureyri.C.list.6.occupation": "Sales Manager",
  "akureyri.C.list.7.occupation": "Physiotherapist",
