  "akureyri.D.list.22.occupation": "Town councillor",
  "akureyri.D.list.3.bio": "Arna Rut Gunnarsdóttir is managing director at the telecommunications company Tengum, 43 years old, with a background as a nurse anaesthetist and a master's degree in health management. She is placed third on the Independence Party list in Akureyri.",
  "akureyri.D.list.3.occupation": "Managing director",
  "akureyri.D.list.4.bio": "Þórhallur Harðarson is executive director of finance and support services at the North Iceland Health Institution and is placed fourth on the Independence Party list in Akureyri. He has held this position for many years and has served as treasurer and chair of the party's constituency council.",
  "akureyri.D.list.4.occupation": "Director of finance and operations",
  "akureyri.D.list.5.bio": "Þorsteinn Kristjánsson is an entrepreneur and is placed fifth on the Independence Party list in Akureyri in the 2026 municipal elections. He brings experience from the business sector to a diverse candidate list with shared priorities for the development of Akureyri.",
  "akureyri.D.list.5.occupation": "Entrepreneur",
