  "akureyri.S.list.22.occupation": "Businessman",
  "akureyri.S.list.3.bio": "Sigrún Steinarsdóttir is the founder of Matargjafir Akureyrar og nágrennis, a social distribution project that has raised over 7 million krónur and assisted more than 200 families, and she is placed third on the Social Democratic Alliance list. Through this initiative, she has become a well-known figure in the fight against poverty in North Iceland.",
  "akureyri.S.list.3.occupation": "Founder of Matargjafir Akureyri",
  "akureyri.S.list.4.bio": "Jóhannes Már Pétursson is a university student in social sciences at the University of Akureyri and is placed fourth on the Social Democratic Alliance list. He has previously served as chair of the international committee and as a representative on the council of the Student Association of the University of Akureyri.",
  "akureyri.S.list.4.occupation": "University Student",
  "akureyri.S.list.5.bio": "Zane Brikovska works at the Bjargey treatment home in Akureyri and is placed fifth on the Social Democratic Alliance list in the 2026 municipal elections. She is of foreign origin and has written about the integration and participation of immigrants in community activities in Akureyri.",
