  "arborg.B.list.8.occupation": "Consultant and embassy employee",
  "arborg.B.list.9.occupation": "Prison officer",
  "arborg.B.tagline": "Progress in Árborg — services and sustainable development in Suðurland",
  "arborg.C.agenda.0.text": "A family-friendly community with a strong school system, accessible preschools, and support for children and parents.",
  "arborg.C.agenda.0.title": "Family-friendly community",
  "arborg.C.agenda.1.text": "Improve road safety, lighting, and the pavement network so that neighbourhoods are safe and convenient.",
  "arborg.C.agenda.1.title": "Safe neighbourhoods",
  "arborg.C.agenda.2.text": "Strengthen services for families facing difficulties and ensure that no one falls through the cracks.",
  "arborg.C.agenda.2.title": "Services for families",
  "arborg.C.agenda.3.text": "Transparent and professional administration in which residents have genuine participation in the decisions that affect their daily lives.",
  "arborg.C.agenda.3.title": "Transparency in decision-making",
  "arborg.C.agenda.4.text": "Leisure grants and equal opportunities for children and young people to participate in sports and the arts regardless of financial circumstances.",
  "arborg.C.agenda.4.title": "Equal opportunities in leisure activities",
  "arborg.C.list.1.bio": "Heiðrún Kristmundsdóttir was born in 1992 and raised on a dairy farm in Skeiðum and Gnúpverjahreppur. She played basketball for Stjarnan and Hamar in Iceland and went to the United States to study basketball at Coker College, where she graduated in 2013. She is a member of the board of the Icelandic Basketball Association. She leads the first Viðreisn list ever to stand in Árborg in the 2026 municipal elections.",
  "arborg.C.list.1.interests.0": "Services for families",
  "arborg.C.list.1.interests.1": "Infrastructure and development in step with growth",
  "arborg.C.list.1.interests.2": "Equal access to services",
