  "arborg.D.agenda.0.text": "Árborg as a family-friendly community where children, parents and older residents enjoy strong services and opportunities.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.0.title": "Family-friendly community",
  "arborg.D.agenda.1.text": "Sensible development and planning that takes account of residents and the municipality’s future growth.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.1.title": "Planning matters",
  "arborg.D.agenda.2.text": "Innovation and entrepreneurship that strengthens a diverse business environment in the Selfoss area.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.2.title": "Innovation",
  "arborg.D.agenda.3.text": "Responsible financial management — reducing debt and improving the financial position creates more room for services.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.3.title": "Responsible finances",
  "arborg.D.agenda.4.text": "A strong public health policy with an emphasis on sports and leisure, physical fitness and prevention.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.4.title": "Public health",
  "arborg.D.agenda.5.text": "Ensure high-quality services, respect and a good life for senior citizens — Árborg should be a good community at every stage of life.",
  "arborg.D.agenda.5.title": "A good place to grow old",
  "arborg.D.list.1.bio": "Bragi Bjarnason was born on 25 April 1981 and is a sports scientist with an MBA degree from the University of Iceland (2020). He has worked for Árborg for 18 years, including as Head of Sports and Leisure, and became Mayor on 1 June 2024. Under his leadership, the town’s operating result has improved significantly — from a deficit of ISK 3.4 billion to a surplus of around ISK 500 million. He leads the Independence Party’s D-list in Árborg.",
  "arborg.D.list.1.interests.0": "Financial balance and debt reduction",
