  "borgarbyggd.M.list.1.bio": "Haukur Þór Hauksson is a business economist and part-time farmer at the farm Fornastekk in Stafholtstungur in Borgarfjörður, where he and his wife, former MP Ásta Möller, settled about a decade ago. For many years he was active in the Independence Party — including as deputy chairman of Heimdallur — but left the party because of dissatisfaction with its cooperation with the Left-Greens in government, which he believed had significantly increased state spending. In business, Haukur has run Borgarljós and the consultancy firm Investis, in addition to serving as chairman of an employers’ association. As the lead candidate of the Centre Party in Borgarbyggð, he places particular emphasis on opposing the planned construction of a wind farm on the Borgarfjörður highlands and the laying of high-voltage power lines through the municipality.",
