  "fjardabyggd.B.list.1.bio": "Þuríður Lillý Sigurðardóttir is a sheep farmer at Slétta in Reyðarfjörður and has served as a Progressive Party town councillor in Fjarðabyggð since 2022. She holds a BS degree in agricultural sciences from the Agricultural University of Iceland at Hvanneyri. On the town council, she has served as chair of the Planning and Works Committee and vice-chair of the Association of Icelandic Municipalities in Austurland. She emphasises responsible financial management, housing development and strengthening core services in the municipality.",
