  "fjardabyggd.M.list.1.bio": "Hrafn Bjarnason is a quality and project manager at Egersund Island in Eskifjörður and completed a BSc degree in fisheries studies from the University of Akureyri in 2012. He worked as a factory manager at Síldarvinnslan hf. from 2013 to 2015 before joining Egersund Island. With professional expertise in production and quality management in the fisheries sector, he has built strong ties to the business community of Austfirðir. He leads the Centre Party’s candidate list in Fjarðabyggð in the 2026 elections.",
