  "gardabaer.D.list.19.occupation": "Public Health Specialist",
  "gardabaer.D.list.2.bio": "Björg Fenger is a lawyer graduated from the University of Iceland and has served as Chair of the Garðabær Town Council Executive Committee since 2022. She has also worked at the Financial Supervisory Authority and the Ministry of Welfare, and is placed second on the Independence Party’s D-list in Garðabær.",
  "gardabaer.D.list.2.occupation": "Chair of the Town Council Executive Committee and lawyer",
  "gardabaer.D.list.20.occupation": "Project Manager",
  "gardabaer.D.list.21.occupation": "Managing Director",
  "gardabaer.D.list.22.occupation": "Managing Director",
  "gardabaer.D.list.3.bio": "Margrét Bjarnadóttir has been President of Garðabær Town Council since 2024 and a town councillor for the Independence Party since 2022. She is studying law at Reykjavík University and is the daughter of Prime Minister Bjarni Benediktsson; she is placed third on the Independence Party’s D-list.",
  "gardabaer.D.list.3.occupation": "President of the Town Council",
  "gardabaer.D.list.4.bio": "Hrannar Bragi Eyjólfsson is a lawyer at Almenni Pension Fund, a town councillor for the Independence Party in Garðabær since 2022, and Chair of the Sports and Leisure Council. He is placed fourth on the Independence Party’s D-list and plays handball for Stjarnan.",
  "gardabaer.D.list.4.occupation": "Town councillor and lawyer",
  "gardabaer.D.list.5.bio": "Stella Stefánsdóttir is a managing director and alternate town councillor for the Independence Party in Garðabær. She holds a master’s degree in innovation and product management and has worked at Össur, Deloitte and Robert Bosch in Germany.",
  "gardabaer.D.list.5.occupation": "Alternate town councillor and managing director",
