  "gardabaer.M.list.1.bio": "Lárus Þór Guðmundsson was born on 12 December 1961 and is a former professional footballer who played in Germany, including for Bayer Uerdingen and 1. FC Kaiserslautern in the 1980s. After his playing career, he returned to Iceland and founded KFG (Knattspyrnufélag Garðabæjar) in 2008. He works as a managing director and is an alternate member of parliament for the Centre Party. Lárus leads the Centre Party’s M-list in Garðabær in the 2026 municipal elections.",
