  "hafnarfjordur.S.agenda.3.text": "Strengthen support for autistic people and safeguard their rights and those of their families in the town.",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.agenda.3.title": "Services for autistic people",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.1.bio": "Guðmundur Árni Stefánsson was born on 31 October 1955 in Hafnarfjörður. He was Mayor of Hafnarfjörður from 1986 to 1993, a member of parliament from 1993 to 2005, Minister of Health and Social Affairs, and Iceland’s ambassador to Sweden, the United States, India and Canada for 17 years. After a long diplomatic career, he returned home to lead the Social Democratic Alliance in Hafnarfjörður and is the party’s deputy chair at national level.",
