  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.2.bio": "Hildur Rós Guðbjargardóttir is a Social Democratic Alliance town councillor in Hafnarfjörður and works at a nursing home while studying to become a primary school teacher. She joined the Social Democratic Alliance in 2016 and has lived in Hafnarfjörður for just over eight years.",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.2.occupation": "Town councillor",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.20.occupation": "Senior citizen",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.21.occupation": "Actor and project manager",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.22.occupation": "Senior citizen",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.3.bio": "Árni Rúnar Þorvaldsson, born in 1976, is a primary school teacher at Smáraskóli in Kópavogur and completed his teacher training at the Iceland University of Education in 2005. He served as a town councillor and chair of the municipal council in Hornafjörður for more than seven years and is now a Social Democratic Alliance town councillor in Hafnarfjörður; he also served as an alternate MP for the party in the Southwest Constituency in 2025.",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.3.occupation": "Town councillor, alternate MP for the Social Democratic Alliance",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.4.bio": "Elín Anna Baldursdóttir is a psychologist and a candidate on the Social Democratic Alliance list in Hafnarfjörður. In April 2026, she published an article on school services without diagnoses.",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.4.occupation": "Psychologist",
  "hafnarfjordur.S.list.5.bio": "Stefán Már Gunnlaugsson is a district priest in Kjalarnesprófastsdæmi and a Social Democratic Alliance town councillor in Hafnarfjörður. He has addressed housing issues for older people in his municipal work and taken part in public debate on community issues.",
