  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.0.text": "A guaranteed preschool place for all children from 12 months of age. Preschool fees reduced by 70%. Waiting lists eliminated with new units in Óskaland in 2025. Six hours a day in preschool free of charge.",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.0.title": "A family-friendly community",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.1.text": "Education at the heart of community development. Continued development of school services and facilities in Hveragerði.",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.1.title": "Education as a cornerstone",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.2.text": "An integrated home care system under the title “Good to Grow Old” in cooperation between the municipality, healthcare services and nursing homes. A youth council established as an advisory committee.",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.2.title": "A welfare system that reaches everyone",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.3.text": "Sustainable development with residents’ welfare as the guiding principle. Financial foundation: a deficit of ISK 356 million (2021) turned into a surplus of ISK 168 million (2024).",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.3.title": "Housing and community development",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.4.text": "Greater transparency in municipal governance. Residents given increased access to decision-making. Local democracy in Þingeying style instead of centralised control from Reykjavík.",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.4.title": "Transparency and local democracy",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.5.text": "Support for a diverse economy and innovation. Marketing the municipality to attract businesses and tourists.",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.agenda.5.title": "New revenue sources and development",
  "hveragerdi.OKH.list.1.bio": "Lárus Jónsson is a basketball coach, sports scientist and holds a master’s degree in international relations. He was elected the new leader of Okkar Hveragerði in March 2026 and heads the list in the municipal elections. Okkar Hveragerði won the 2022 election, and Lárus has pledged to continue that journey with professional working methods and positive communication.",
