  "kopavogur.B.agenda.0.text": "Ensure preschool places for all children from 12 months of age — eliminate the waiting list issue that has burdened families.",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.0.title": "Preschool places from 12 months",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.1.text": "Increase the number of psychologists, guidance counsellors and support staff in schools — services for children who need them must be in place.",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.1.title": "Stronger support in primary schools",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.2.text": "Promote the physical and social wellbeing of older people in Kópavogur — more leisure opportunities, home care services and community connections.",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.2.title": "Social wellbeing of older residents",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.3.text": "Manage the town’s finances carefully and ensure that development plans are financed in a sustainable way.",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.3.title": "Responsible financial management",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.4.text": "Advocate lower fees and better services — improve conditions for families in Kópavogur during the council term.",
  "kopavogur.B.agenda.4.title": "Households first",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.bio": "Orri Vignir Hlöðversson completed a BA degree in international affairs and economics from the University of California in 1993. He worked in Brussels for the European Commission and the US Embassy. He was Mayor of Hveragerði from 2002 to 2006 and has lived in Kópavogur for 15 years. He is Managing Director and a shareholder in Frumherji hf.",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.interests.0": "Employment and innovation",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.interests.1": "Education and preschools",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.interests.2": "Transport issues",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.interests.3": "Efficient operation of the municipality",
  "kopavogur.B.list.1.occupation": "Managing Director, Town Councillor",
