  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.19.occupation": "Candidate",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.2.bio": "Guðný Maja Riba is a teacher and has served on Reykjavík City Executive Council on behalf of the Social Democratic Alliance; she also ran for deputy chair of the Icelandic Teachers’ Union in 2021. She is now moving to Mosfellsbær and is in second place on the Social Democratic Alliance list there.",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.2.occupation": "Teacher and town councillor",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.20.occupation": "Candidate",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.21.occupation": "Candidate",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.22.occupation": "Candidate",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.3.bio": "Ómar Ingþórsson is a landscape architect and natural scientist; he received his licence as a landscape architect in 2005. He is in third place on the Social Democratic Alliance list in Mosfellsbær and has written about transport and planning issues in the town.",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.3.occupation": "Landscape architect and natural scientist",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.4.bio": "Auður Einarsdóttir is a law student. She is in fourth place on the Social Democratic Alliance list in Mosfellsbær in the 2026 municipal elections.",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.4.occupation": "Law student",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.5.bio": "Guðlaugur Bjarki Lúðvíksson is an engineer and head of Norðurál’s safety, environment and improvement division. He is also involved in teaching at the University of Iceland in industrial and mechanical engineering.",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.5.occupation": "Engineer",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.6.occupation": "Special education teacher",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.7.occupation": "Political science student",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.8.occupation": "University student",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.list.9.occupation": "Office manager at Þroskahjálp",
  "mosfellsbaer.S.tagline": "Ólafur Ingi leads the Social Democratic Alliance in Mosfellsbær",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.0.text": "Advocate for the Fjarðarheiðargöng tunnel project and Axarvegur road works — projects awaiting action in the transport plan.",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.0.title": "Road projects",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.1.text": "Oppose the centralisation of health inspection to Reykjavík; maintain a well-functioning regional system.",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.1.title": "Health inspection",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.2.text": "Support new allocations for coastal fishing, but oppose cuts to longline-related permits and regional quotas.",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.2.title": "Fisheries",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.3.text": "Oppose the increase in VAT on steam baths and hot springs, which weakens winter tourism in rural areas.",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.3.title": "Tourism and taxation",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.4.text": "Ensure equal treatment, residential development and long-term development opportunities for rural areas in the face of centralising pressure.",
  "mulathing.B.agenda.4.title": "Equality in rural areas",
  "mulathing.B.list.1.bio": "Jónína Brynjólfsdóttir is a commercial lawyer with a master’s degree in management and leadership studies and has lived in Egilsstaðir for just over 14 years, originally from Reykjavík. She works as a museum director and also serves as President of the Municipal Council of Múlaþing. She served as a substitute MP for the Progressive Party (Northeast Constituency) in May and July 2025. Jónína places emphasis on advocating for rural areas, transport and healthcare services in Austurland.",
