  "mulathing.D.agenda.2.title": "Transport",
  "mulathing.D.list.1.bio": "Berglind Harpa Svavarsdóttir was born on 28 November 1975 and is a trained nurse. She has eight years of experience in local government — as chair of the municipal executive council of Múlaþing and former chair of the Association of Municipalities in Austurland (SSA). Berglind is a deputy MP for the Independence Party in the Northeast Constituency and has sat in parliament seven times since 2021. She received 219 votes in the party’s primary on 28 February 2026, securing first place on the list.",
