  "mulathing.L.agenda.0.text": "Give children and young people priority — improve mental health services and ensure equal access regardless of where they live.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.0.title": "Services for children and young people",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.1.text": "Strengthen cooperation between schools across municipalities in Austurland and ensure equal quality education in all districts.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.1.title": "Education and school cooperation",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.2.text": "Accelerate transport infrastructure development in Austurland — Fjarðarheiðargöng, Axarvegur and better connections for rural areas.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.2.title": "Transport",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.3.text": "A cross-institutional approach in which healthcare, education and social services work together on comprehensive solutions.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.3.title": "Cross-institutional cooperation",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.4.text": "Transparent and responsible financial management that ensures scope for development without cutting essential services.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.4.title": "Responsible financial management",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.5.text": "Oppose centralisation and service cuts that run counter to fairness towards Austurland.",
  "mulathing.L.agenda.5.title": "Regional justice",
  "mulathing.L.list.1.bio": "Hólmfríður Rut Einarsdóttir is a communications and marketing consultant from Egilsstaðir. She was the lead candidate for Viðreisn in Múlaþing before Austurlistinn and Viðreisn merged into a single joint list in April 2026. In April 2026, she wrote an opinion piece urging that children and young people be given priority in municipal affairs. Hólmfríður now leads the joint list of Austurlistinn and Viðreisn in Múlaþing.",
