  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.0.text": "Increase preschool places by more than 200 during the term — solve the waiting list problem that is weighing heavily on families in Reykjanesbær.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.0.title": "200+ more preschool places",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.1.text": "Introduce a leisure grant scheme for older people — promote active participation and a healthy way of life.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.1.title": "Leisure grant for senior citizens",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.2.text": "Ensure the town’s finances remain stable and create room for development without accumulating debt.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.2.title": "Responsible financial management",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.3.text": "Oppose centralisation and ensure that Suðurnes receives its fair share in national development.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.3.title": "We are, after all, the regions",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.4.text": "More open and transparent consultation processes in which residents have a real influence on the town’s development and future vision.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.agenda.4.title": "Consultation with residents",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.1.bio": "Halldóra Fríða Þorvaldsdóttir was born on 8 May 1980 and works as a project manager for Icelandic as a second language in Reykjanesbær. She is trained as a primary school teacher and specialised in teaching blind and visually impaired students at the University of Birmingham. She has over 20 years of experience in education and welfare services and has served as a Framsókn town councillor in Reykjanesbær and as a substitute MP in 2022–2023. She leads Framsókn’s B-list in the 2026 municipal elections.",
