  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.2.bio": "Róbert Jóhann Guðmundsson is a master painter and co-owner of Málningarþjónustu JRJ ehf., which he founded in 2004. He was born and raised in Keflavík and has lived in Njarðvík since 2001. He served as a Framsókn representative on Reykjanesbær’s Environment and Planning Council for four years and sits on the board of Húsasmíðameistara Suðurnesja.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.2.occupation": "Town councillor and master painter",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.20.occupation": "Lawyer",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.21.occupation": "Former town councillor",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.22.occupation": "Substitute MP",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.3.bio": "Díana Hilmarsdóttir is the director of Björgin, the mental health centre of Suðurnes in Reykjanesbær. She holds a BA degree in social work from the University of Iceland and serves as a Framsókn town councillor in Reykjanesbær.",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.3.occupation": "Town councillor and director of Björgin",
  "reykjanesbaer.B.list.4.bio": "Birgir Már Bragasson is the managing director of Keflavík, a sports and youth association (ÍUK). He is fourth on Framsókn’s candidate list in Reykjanesbær for the 2026 municipal elections.",
