  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.0.text": "Lower property taxes and municipal income tax — easing the burden on families who moved from Grindavík.",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.0.title": "Lower taxes",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.1.text": "A more diverse and more affordable housing supply in Reykjanesbær.",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.1.title": "Housing",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.2.text": "Renew and strengthen the municipality’s library.",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.2.title": "Library",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.3.text": "Professional and efficient core services — schools, preschools and transport.",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.agenda.3.title": "Core services",
  "reykjanesbaer.D.list.1.bio": "Vilhjálmur Árnason was born on 29 October 1983 in Sauðárkrókur. He has been a Member of Alþingi for the South Constituency for the Independence Party since 2013, and previously served as a police officer in Suðurnes for just over a decade. He holds a BA degree and a master’s degree in law from Reykjavík University and has served as treasurer of the Independence Party since 2022. He moved with his family from Grindavík to Reykjanesbær because of the volcanic eruptions and won the D-list primary with 1,037 votes.",
