  "reykjanesbaer.M.list.1.bio": "Gunnlaugur Kárason was born on 13 July 1976 in Suðurnes. He holds qualifications in business studies and teaching, and has a varied career background: he has taught and managed a primary school, worked in banking for 6 years, and then in the energy sector for 10 years, including as Chief Financial Officer of HS Veitur. He now runs his own consultancy and finance company, Opulent. He has served as a deputy town councillor in Reykjanesbær and leads the M-list of the Centre Party in 2026.",
