  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.19.occupation": "Chair of the Reykjanesbær Council of Elders",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.2.bio": "Hjörtur Magnús Guðbjartsson works as a systems administrator. He has served as a Social Democratic Alliance councillor in Reykjanesbær and is Chair of the Board of Reykjaneshöfn.",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.2.occupation": "Systems administrator",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.20.occupation": "Former Chief Engineer and Alternate Board Member of the Association of Senior Citizens",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.21.occupation": "Former Town Councillor and Student of Herbal Medicine",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.22.occupation": "Former Town Councillor and Consultant",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.3.bio": "Aðalheiður Hilmarsdóttir is an employment and activation adviser at the City of Reykjavík. She has served as an alternate councillor for the Social Democratic Alliance in Reykjanesbær and has specialist expertise in employment and welfare issues.",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.3.occupation": "Employment and activation adviser at the City of Reykjavík",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.4.bio": "Bjarni Halldór Heiðuson Janusson is a political scientist and in 2017 became the youngest substitute MP in Iceland’s history when he took a seat in Alþingi for Viðreisn, aged 21 years and 142 days. He was among the founders of Viðreisn in 2014 and the first chair of the party’s youth movement; in January 2026 he joined the Social Democratic Alliance and is fourth on its list in Reykjanesbær.",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.4.occupation": "Political scientist",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.5.bio": "Hámundur Örn Helgason is Managing Director of Ungmennafélagið Njarðvík (UMFN), a sports club in Reykjanesbær. He has also served as sports and operations manager and has appeared at meetings of the Reykjanesbær Town Council in connection with sports matters.",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.5.occupation": "Managing Director of UMFN",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.6.occupation": "Councillor and police officer",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.7.occupation": "Communications Director at VIRK",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.8.occupation": "Public health scientist and teacher",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.list.9.occupation": "Developmental therapist",
  "reykjanesbaer.S.tagline": "Guðný Birna leads the Social Democratic Alliance in Reykjanesbær",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.0.text": "Reykjavík as a city of peace built on democratic values, equality, sustainability and social justice — where all residents can have a home and access services.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.0.title": "Reykjavík for all of us",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.1.text": "Housing should be homes, built for people rather than investors. Increased supply through a social housing association, renovation of older housing and accessibility for all.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.1.title": "Homes and housing",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.2.text": "A stronger bus system, free travel for primary school children and implementation of the rail project to reduce traffic and pollution.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.2.title": "Transport",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.3.text": "Free school meals, more daycare places, better terms for staff and improved access to specialist services in schools — interpreters, psychologists, speech therapists.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.3.title": "Education and equality",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.4.text": "A vibrant cultural life with accessible public spaces, arts and entertainment. Support for artists through grants and subsidised rental spaces.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.4.title": "Culture and quality of life",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.5.text": "Strengthen sports centres and youth work, protect marginalised groups, advance the rights of LGBTQ+ people and immigrants, and reduce poverty.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.5.title": "Community life and welfare",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.6.text": "Protect valuable natural areas in the city through stronger water protection and biodiversity measures — allowing wild animals to thrive in the urban environment.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.6.title": "Nature conservation in Reykjavík",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.7.text": "Ensure decent pay, working conditions and safety for all employees. Oppose the outsourcing of services and safeguard direct municipal jobs.",
  "reykjavik.A.agenda.7.title": "Reykjavík as a workplace",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.bio": "Sanna Magdalena Mörtudóttir was born on 3 May 1992 and is an anthropologist and leader of the Socialist Party of Iceland since October 2024. She was elected to Reykjavík City Council in 2018 and became the youngest city councillor in the city's history. She is of Icelandic and Tanzanian heritage and leads the joint list of VG and Vor til vinstri, called The Left.",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.interests.0": "Equality and human rights",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.interests.1": "Housing and social justice",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.interests.2": "The fight against poverty",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.interests.3": "Issues affecting marginalised groups",
  "reykjavik.A.list.1.occupation": "Anthropologist, City Councillor (Vor til vinstri)",
