  "reykjavik.B.list.19.occupation": "Musician, university student",
  "reykjavik.B.list.2.bio": "Magnea Gná Jóhannsdóttir was born on 3 April 1997 and became the youngest City Councillor in Reykjavík’s history when she was elected in 2022, at just 25 years old. She completed a BA degree in law at the University of Iceland in 2021 and is now pursuing a master’s degree. She was chair of Ung Framsókn in Reykjavík.",
  "reykjavik.B.list.2.interests.0": "Law and human rights",
