  "reykjavik.D.list.2.bio": "Bjarni Eggerts Guðjónsson was born on 26 February 1979 and is a former professional footballer who played, among other clubs, for Newcastle United and Stoke City. After his playing career, he worked as a coach and managing director of KR for three years, and completed a BS degree in business administration from Reykjavík University. He worked at VÍS Insurance before standing in the 2026 municipal elections.",
