  "reykjavik.D.list.5.bio": "Rúnar Freyr Gíslason was born on 29 April 1973 and is a well-known Icelandic actor and voice actor. He graduated from the Icelandic Drama School in 1999 and has appeared in numerous productions at the National Theatre. He is known for roles in the series Ófærð and Trapped and has directed productions of Söngvakeppnin.",
