  "reykjavik.G.agenda.0.text": "Simplify the city’s organisation, streamline operations and reduce debt accumulation.",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.0.title": "Organisation and operations",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.1.text": "Special emphasis on security in operations and sound administrative practices.",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.1.title": "Operational security",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.2.text": "Listen to city residents — regular opinion surveys and better communication with residents.",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.2.title": "Resident consultation",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.3.text": "Opposition to the original Borgarlína plan; support for Sundagangur (a tunnel instead of a bridge).",
  "reykjavik.G.agenda.3.title": "Transport",
  "reykjavik.G.list.1.bio": "Ingimar Þór Friðriksson is an entrepreneur and computer scientist. He completed a BSc in computer science from Háskóli Íslands in 1989 and an MBA from Háskólinn í Reykjavík in 2002. He served as head of the information technology department of Kópavogsbær from 2011 to 2025 and now leads the Góðan daginn candidacy.",
