  "reykjavik.J.agenda.0.text": "Establish a city-run building association to build and operate non-profit housing; the city’s plots should be used for social development.",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.0.title": "Housing",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.1.text": "Transfer the operation of public transport into the hands of the city, lower fares and improve connections; oppose private operation in parking matters.",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.1.title": "Transport",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.2.text": "Strengthen support services within schools and increase the number of specialists; place greater emphasis on Icelandic language teaching, leisure activities and school meals.",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.2.title": "Education",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.3.text": "Reykjavíkurborg should establish its own grocery shops to counter high prices; end the outsourcing of the city’s projects.",
  "reykjavik.J.agenda.3.title": "Food policy and welfare",
  "reykjavik.J.list.1.bio": "Silja Sóley Birgisdóttir was born on 13 May 2000 and heads the list of Sósíalistaflokkur Íslands in Reykjavík. She was approved at a members’ meeting of Jafnaðarmannafélag Reykjavíkur on 7 February 2026. She has appeared in numerous interviews on housing and school issues.",
