  "reykjavik.M.agenda.0.text": "Opposes the current Borgarlína plans as \"strange ideas\"; calls for a complete review of the city's transport plan from the ground up.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.0.title": "Against Borgarlína",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.1.text": "\"Parking has become a luxury product\" — calls for car accessibility; opposes car-free zones in the city centre.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.1.title": "Parking issues",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.2.text": "Core municipal services (schools, preschools, care) must take priority over major capital investments.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.2.title": "Core services first",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.3.text": "Criticises the city's accumulated debt and declining municipal fund; calls for better financial management.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.3.title": "Financial responsibility",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.4.text": "Improved compulsory and upper secondary schools; Reykjavík's preschool system has the worst results.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.4.title": "Education",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.5.text": "Prevent damage caused by the Suðurlandsbraut expansion; opposes disruptive large-scale infrastructure.",
  "reykjavik.M.agenda.5.title": "Infrastructure",
