  "reykjavik.S.agenda.0.text": "Administration geared to the needs of residents; people put first in all decisions in Reykjavík.",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.0.title": "A city for people",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.1.text": "A strong emphasis on a vibrant cultural life, with increased funding for cultural affairs.",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.1.title": "Cultural life",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.2.text": "Each child’s leisure grant increased from ISK 50,000 to ISK 75,000; support for the quality of preschools; free school camps.",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.2.title": "Education and youth",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.3.text": "Make city services more accessible and less bureaucratic; reduce hassle in parking, paths and planning matters.",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.3.title": "Accessible services",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.4.text": "A city of equality, human rights, quality of life and sustainability; a multicultural policy.",
