  "reykjavik.S.agenda.5.text": "Free bus travel for children under 16.",
  "reykjavik.S.agenda.5.title": "Strætó for children",
  "reykjavik.S.list.1.bio": "Pétur Hafliði Marteinsson was born on 14 July 1973 and grew up in Breiðholt in Reykjavík. He is a former professional footballer who played, among other clubs, for Hammarby IF and Stoke City, and earned 36 caps for the Iceland national team. After his sporting career, he completed an MBA and now works as an operations manager.",
  "reykjavik.S.list.1.interests.0": "Preschool issues and increasing places",
